Point Spread Odds: Utah St -24 
Notes: When these teams met in 2014 it was Utah St with the 20-3 road victory at Wyoming as a -7 ½ point wagering favorite. The total went under 48 points. Wyoming falls to 1-7 with the 34-14 road defeat last week to the Boise St Broncos as a +34 point betting underdog. The game went under 60 points. The Cowboys offense gained just 233 yards with 123 passing yards. On defense Wyoming allowed 211 passing yards and three touchdown throws by Broncos quarterback Brett Rypien. 
Utah St is 4-3 following the 48-14 road defeat last week to the San Diego St Aztecs as a -4 point wagering favorite. The game went over 43 ½ points. The Aggies gained just 239 offensive yards and were down 34-7 at the half. They threw for just 95 yards and had four turnovers and a -4 margin for the game. On defense they allowed the Aztecs offense 429 yards with 336 rushing for 5 ½ yards per carry. Utah St is 115th in the nation in total offense with 338 yards averaged per game.
